Compare_cohorts

Quynh Tran

November 4, 2015

This script was most recently run on Fri Nov 6 17:48:30 2015. This script is to compare the mice body weight across different cohorts. The script also explores the relationship between initial weight, weight loss and the weights after HFD.

Weight data from cohort 5 and 6 were read in from ../data/processed/fasting_weights_file.csv.

Weight data from cohort 8 and 9 were read in from ../data/raw/Cohort_8_Raw_Data.csv and ../data/raw/Cohort_9_Raw_Data.csv.

Tukey post-hoc analysis of body weight

[1] Tukeys post-hoc pairwise comparisons of Ininital weight [1] Tukeys post-hoc pairwise comparisons of Fasted weight [1] Tukeys post-hoc pairwise comparisons of Fasted weight

Overall, body weight appeared to be normally distributed across different feeding stages, except for cohort 5. This may be due to one or two mice with outlier weights.

Checking the normality of weight loss and weight gain
